epics.summary: The different project entities their relations and the logic
Ability to configure recommended, featured and main articles
Planning the project's server and client
General components in the project, framework, DB type, etc
The different entities and their relations, procedures, queries
Intro screen, splash, terms of use, welcome screen (first use)
The home page: last session, navigate to setting
Settings: personal info, push notifications,event mode acces,

As a user, once I open the app I will see a splash screen.
As a user at first use, I will see the intro screens.
As a user, I will be able to swipe between the intro screens.
As a user, at the last intro screen I will be able to move on to see the feed.
As a user, I will see the login screen.
As a user, I will be able to navigate to the signup screen.
As a user, I will be able to sign in via several options.
As a user that forgot his password, I will be able to restore my password.
As a user, I will see the signup screen.
As a user, if I choose to sign up I will be able to sign up via several options.
As a user in the signup process, I will have to fill in my profile data in order to complete the process.
As a user, I will be able to navigate to the “terms of use” screen.
As a user, I will navigate to the profile video screen by signing up.
As a user, I will enter the first Profile Video recording page.
As a user that tapped on the recording icon, I will start to record my profile video.
As a user, I will be able to confirm or not confirm my video.
As a user, all “profile pictures” I see are GIFs, derived from the profile video.
As a user, I will enter the main feed and see all of the category questions and the most popular answer (1) of each question.
As a user I will be able to use the header to direct me to my profile page and navigate between categories.
As a user, I will be able to see the questions section.
As a user, I will see a call-to-action message if there is no answer for a question.
As a returning user, the feed will present the last category I’ve visited.
As a user, I will be able to record my answer.
As a user, I will be able to pause an answer video.
As a user, I will see the question page.
As a user, by tapping on the “X” button I will return to the previous screen.
As a user, I will see the answer header and video
As a user, I will be able to comment on a video.
As a user, I will be able to view which other users viewed the video.
As a user, I will be able to like an answer and view who liked it.
As a user, I will be able to record my answer.
As a user, I will be able to pause an answer.
As a user, I will be able to share the answer in facebook.
As a user I will be able to view my profile video.
As a user I will be able to navigate to several screens.
As a user, I will be able to see several data about my engagements.
As a user, I will have 2 option of viewing my videos.
As a user, I will be able to navigate to several screens.
As a user, I will be able to turn off\on my notifications settings.
As a user I will be able to read more about TS
As a user I will be able to read terms of use.
As a user, I will be able to contact TownSquare.
As a user, I will be able to invite friends to the app.
As a user, I will be able to suggest a question.
As a user, I will be able to log out of TS
As a user I will be able to view other user's profile.
As a user I will be able to navigate to several screens.
As a user, I will be able to see several data about the user’s engagements.
As a user, I will have 2 option of viewing the user’s videos.
As a user, I will be able to share the answer in facebook.
As a user without an internet connection I will be notified whenever an action that requires internet will fail.
As a user that has closed the app, when I return to the app I will be directed to the first screen. If I  moved the app to the background, when I come back I will return to the last seen page.
